comments.body:
This technique works most of the time but relies on undefined behavior.   It is for example likely to fails in the example:
```
{
   auto c = new TCanvas("canvas", "canvas"); // gPad=c;
   auto p = new TPad("pad", "pad", .2, .05, .8, .35 ); // fMother = gPad = c;
   delete c;
   auto other = new ClassSlightlySmallerThanTCanvas(....);
   p->Close(); 
}
```
where it might fails because the other objects is reusing the memory previously used by the TCanvas ...

